{
  "texts": [
    "We conducted tests in various environments, especially including low illumination and occasional camera shaking conditions.",
    "On average, our recognition network achieves a Top-1 accuracy rate of 48.53% and a Top-5 accuracy rate of 61.83% across 3200 classes, indicating the robustness of our recognition algorithm.F v = F pose + (1 -)F RGB, Sign language detectionWe need a sign language detection (SLD) model to determine when the sign language user begins signing in the inputted real-time video.",
    "SLD [28,32] is defined as the binary classification task for any given frame of a video if a person is using sign language or not.",
    "Given that the SLD task demands high model efficiency, we employ the SL-GCN [16] as the backbone of our model.",
    "Following the approach outlined in [28], we initially pre-train on the Public DGS Corpus [33]."
  ]
}